    {
      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<p class=\"alert alert-info\"><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-blue120\">This content is available to customers with active <a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/en-us/articles/360014400932\" target=\"_self\">Liferay Enterprise Search (LES)</a> subscriptions</span></p>\n<p>Published: June 7, 2019</p>\n<p>The following issue may affect the functionality of your Liferay Enterprise Search environment. This notification provides a description of the latest compatibility change and required actions for Liferay Enterprise Search Subscribers.</p>\n<p><strong>If you’re running an Elasticsearch cluster version 2.2.x or 2.4.x, AND utilize AWS S3 for snapshots, you will need to prepare for Amazon’s deprecation of the S3 Sigv2 API.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Deployments which might be impacted by this change</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Liferay DXP 7.0 on Elastic Stack 2.2.x and 2.4.x using S3 snapshots</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Compatibility Change Information</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://link.elastic.co/f009p2e0pA01BA3xMBMRQ0j?utm_source=hs_email&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;_hsenc=p2ANqtz-8BF_tL0ZonhuGU3F3-2WDDlAOaHxCb4Yqxp1cXwU8e5QrSbcHUMCkNvUTeGkH20CuFr0Bc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\">AWS service changes to go into effect on June 24, 2019</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/en-us/articles/360028942772?utm_source=hs_email&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;_hsenc=p2ANqtz-8BF_tL0ZonhuGU3F3-2WDDlAOaHxCb4Yqxp1cXwU8e5QrSbcHUMCkNvUTeGkH20CuFr0Bc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\">Liferay Knowledge Base article</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Liferay Enterprise Search Compatibility Matrix</strong></p>\n<p>Reference the information <a href=\"/w/search-engine-compatibility-matrix\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\">here</a><span> </span>to learn more about the supported configurations for Liferay Enterprise Search.</p>"
      },
